1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,129
Leadership rule number three.

2
00:00:02,320 --> 00:00:06,929
Think progress, believe in progress, push for progress.

3
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:14,210
One of the most complimentary things anyone can say about you is, he stands for progress.

4
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:16,369
He's the man for the job.

5
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:23,490
Promotions in all fields go to individuals who believe in and push for progress.

6
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:27,409
Leaders, real leaders, are in short supply.

7
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:33,730
Status-quoers, the everything's alright, let's don't upset the apple cart folks,

8
00:00:33,920 --> 00:00:41,090
far outnumber the progressives, the there's lots of room for improvement, let's get to work and do it better people.

9
00:00:41,359 --> 00:00:43,409
Join the leadership elite.

10
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:45,490
Develop a forward look.

11
00:00:46,960 --> 00:00:51,730
There are two special things you can do to develop your progressive outlook.

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,409
One, think improvement in everything you do.

13
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:59,330
Two, think high standards in everything you do.

14
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:08,210
Several months ago, the president of a medium-sized company asked me to help him make an important decision.

15
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:14,369
This executive had built the business by himself and had been functioning as sales manager.

16
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:23,250
Now, with seven salesmen employed, he decided his next step was to promote one of his salesmen to the job of sales manager.

17
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:31,010
He narrowed the choice down to three, all of whom were about equal in experience and sales performance.

18
00:01:31,599 --> 00:01:41,330
My assignment was to spend one day in the field with each man and then report my views on which fellow seemed to be best qualified to lead the group.

19
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:47,649
Each man was told that a consultant would visit him to discuss the overall marketing program.

20
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:53,010
For obvious reasons, they were not told the specific purpose of my visit.

21
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:56,849
Two of the men reacted pretty much the same way.

22
00:01:56,960 --> 00:01:59,169
Both were uncomfortable with me.

23
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:02,849
They seemed to sense that I was there to change things.

24
00:02:03,119 --> 00:02:07,010
Each of these men was a real defender of the status quo.

25
00:02:07,359 --> 00:02:10,609
Both approved of the way everything was being done.

26
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:16,210
I raised questions about how the territories were laid out, the compensation program,

27
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:20,530
the sales promotional material, every facet of the marketing effort.

28
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:24,849
But on all points, the response was always, everything is okay.

29
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:31,730
On specific points, these two men explained why the present way couldn't and shouldn't be changed.

30
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:37,250
Summed up, both men wanted the status quo to remain the status quo.

31
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:41,010
One of them said to me as he dropped me by my hotel,

32
00:02:41,359 --> 00:02:48,129
I don't know exactly why you spent the day with me, but tell Mr. M for me that everything is okay as is.

33
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:50,530
Don't go refiguring anything.

34
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,889
The third man was wonderfully different.

35
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:59,520
He was pleased with the company and proud of its growth, but he was not wholly content.
